A 43-year-old man was sentenced to life imprisonment for raping his 15-year-old niece. Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said the man was sentenced on Tuesday at the Port Shepstone Regional Court. ALSO READ | Family lives in fear after child’s rape Mbele said the man’s sentence came after the court heard how he brutally raped his 15-year-old niece on the afternoon of December 21 last year. “A 15-year-old girl was asleep at her home at the Boboyi area when she was awoken by her uncle. The accused locked all the doors and he assaulted and repeatedly raped the victim until he fell asleep." The teen managed to escape and get help. "A case of rape was opened at Port Shepstone SAPS. The docket was transferred to Port Shepstone Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit and the accused was placed under arrest,” said Mbele. ALSO READ | Suspect (47) in court for rape of girl (6) She said the man’s name will be included in the National Offenders Register and he was declared unfit to possess a firearm “This sentence will send a strong message to other rapists who are victimising defenceless women and children and think that they will get away,” said the KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula.